%N A397372 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} (zeta(2) - H(2*k,2))*H(k)/k, where H(k) = A001008(k)/A002805(k) is the k-th harmonic number, and H(k,2) = A007406(k)/A007407(k) is the k-th generalized harmonic number of order 2.
%H A397372 Cornel Ioan Vălean, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-21262-8">More (Almost) Impossible Integrals, Sums, and Series</a>, Springer Cham, 2023. See section 4.26, p. 429, eq. (4.117), section 5.26, p. 462, section 6.26, pp. 635-636.
%H A397372 <a href="/index/Ha#harmonic">Index entries for sequences related to harmonic numbers</a>.
%F A397372 Equals log(2)^4/3 - log(2)^2*zeta(2)/2 + 7*log(2)*zeta(3)/2 - 21*zeta(4)/4 + 8*Li_4(1/2).
